Task: Rust specifying a trait and associated type are valid for the lifetime inside a function

 <p>I am using the <code>winnow</code> crate to write a parser and am struggling with
adding tests due to lifetime conflicts.</p>
<p>The basic setup I have is a stateful stream:</p>
<pre class="lang-rs prettyprint-override"><code>// The primary stream type
type SStream&lt;'i, 'e&gt; = Stateful&lt;LocatingSlice&lt;&amp;'i str&gt;, State&lt;'e&gt;&gt;;

#[derive(Debug)]
struct State&lt;'e&gt; {
